# RE-IA — Revenue Ecosystem IA
# Documentação canônica: docs/README.md (00-vision through 14-deploy)

project_type: Python Modular Revenue Ecosystem
architecture: Clean Architecture simplified — NO queues, events, or DDD in MVP
python: "3.11+"

constraints:
  - Gemini MUST pass through shared_components cache (semantic + hash) before any API call
  - similarity_threshold: 0.96
  - embeddings: sentence-transformers on CPU only
  - no_paid_apis_in_ingestion: true
  - deterministic_first: true
  - no_cross_module_imports: true

implementation_order:
  1. shared_components (cache, database, gemini_client, compliance)
  2. modules/01_opportunity_finder
  3. modules/02_affiliate_saas
  4. modules/03_notion_funnel
  5. dashboard Streamlit (phase 4 only)

coding:
  type_hints: required
  schemas: Pydantic
  tests: pytest for shared_components
  format: black + isort

before_coding:
  - Read relevant doc in docs/ (03-modules for module work)
  - One backlog item per session (docs/11-backlog.md)
  - Never add features without ROI justification

prohibited:
  - DDD, CQRS, event bus, Redis/Celery in MVP
  - Direct Gemini calls bypassing gemini_client
  - New modules before revenue from 02 or 03
  - Paid APIs in data ingestion layer
